## This repository includes the data used for the master thesis: "A Digital Humanities Approach to Characterizing Murderers in Agatha Christieâ€™s Detective Novels". 
## This thesis argues that the results from distant reading aligns with  Agatha Christie's conception of murderers in previous researches(through close reading) and her moderate feminism.
## The content of this github repository includes following data structure:
### primary literature: eight selected novels by Agatha Christie
### visualizations of social network analysis using Gephi 
### barplot of speech/appearance rate using R, with the code in R.data format
### visualization of the results of sentiment analysis and linguistic representation
### t-sne visualiaztions of the murderers in these eight novels
